						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vīrarājēndra Year 4 <hi rend="italic">Mīna</hi>, śu. di. 12. Sunday = 8th March 1248 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 2 <hi rend="italic">māḍai</hi> by an individual, Araśāṇḍai, a resident of Pūṇḍi in order to burn two twilight lamps to the god Nīrvaṇṇan Tirunīrmalai-nāyanār temple. The temple priest Naimisai Yagñanārāyaṇa Bhaṭṭ[aṉ] received the gift and agreed to burn the lamp perpetually.</p>						

						</summary>
